iOFanTable.name: iOFanTable
iOFanTable.description: Table of status information about all Instant Office cooling fans

iOFanEntry.name: iOFanEntry
iOFanEntry.description: An entry in the Fan Table.

fanIndex.name: fanIndex
fanIndex.description: The index of the cooling fan within the system

fanOperStatus.name: fanOperStatus
fanOperStatus.description: The operational status of this fan. The following are valid values: running =1,(the normal operational state), stopped =2, unknown =3

iOPSTable.name: iOPSTable
iOPSTable.description: Table of status information about all Instant Office power supplies

iOPSEntry.name: iOPSEntry
iOPSEntry.description: An entry in the Power Supply Table.

psIndex.name: psIndex
psIndex.description: The index of the power supply unit within the system

psOperStatus.name: psOperStatus
psOperStatus.description: The operational status of this power supply. The following are valid values: on=1, off=2, unknown=3

iOFaultMonitorStatus.name: iOFaultMonitorStatus
iOFaultMonitorStatus.description: The operational status of the Fault Monitor. The following are valid values: RAMFull =1, NotResponding =2, Ok =3, ModemFailed =4

iOLastFanTrap.name: iOLastFanTrap
iOLastFanTrap.description: This object describes,in more detail,the last Fan Trap event that occured. Since traps for all fans are combined into one Trap, this string describes each fan status just after the trap condition.

iOLastPowerSupplyTrap.name: iOLastPowerSupplyTrap
iOLastPowerSupplyTrap.description: This object describes,in more detail,the last Power Supply Trap event that occured. Since traps for all power supplies are combined into one Trap, this string describes each power supply status just after the trap condition.

iOLastFaultMonitorTrap.name: iOLastFaultMonitorTrap
iOLastFaultMonitorTrap.description: This object describes,in more detail,the last Fault Monitor Trap event that occured. Since traps for all Fault Monitor events are combined into one Trap,this string describes the Fault Monitor event (RAM full, NotResponding or Modem Failed) that caused this trap.

iOFanStatus.name: iOFanStatus
iOFanStatus.description: This notification is sent when one (or more) cooling fans changes state (i.e. it goes from an ON state to OFF state or vice-versa. Even if more than one fan changes state, only one trap is sent. Information about the new state of all the fans is sent in the Trap Data (iOLastFanTrap)

iOPowerSupplyStatus.name: iOPowerSupplyStatus
iOPowerSupplyStatus.description: This notification is sent when one (or more) power supply units changs state (i.e it goes from an ON state to an OFF state, or vice versa). Even if more than one power supply changes state, only one trap is sent. Information about the new state of all the power supplies is sent in the Trap Data (IOLastPowerSupplyTrap).

iOFaultMonitorStatusTrap.name: iOFaultMonitorStatusTrap
iOFaultMonitorStatusTrap.description: This notification is sent when or more of the following Fault Monitor Events occur: RAM full, Fault Monitor NotResponding or Modem Failed. Information about these events is contained in the Trap data (IOLatFaultmonitorTrap).
